    <h1>Understanding HTML Tags in Blogging</h1>

    <!-- Introduction -->
    <p>
        Welcome to this tutorial on HTML tags used in blogging! Here, we’ll explore essential tags like anchor tags, title tags, and more.
    </p>

    <!-- Anchor Tag Example -->
    <h2>What is an Anchor Tag?</h2>
    <p>
        An <strong>anchor tag</strong> (<code>&lt;a&gt;</code>) is used to create hyperlinks in HTML. Here’s an example:
    </p>
    <p>
        Visit <a href="https://www.w3schools.com" target="_blank" title="W3Schools Online Tutorials">W3Schools</a> to learn more about HTML.
    </p>

    <!-- Image Example -->
    <h2>Adding Images with Alt Text</h2>
    <p>Images make your blog more appealing. Here’s an example of an image with alt text:</p>
    <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/600x300" alt="Placeholder image for demonstration" width="600">

    <!-- Table Example -->
    <h2>Using Tables to Organize Information</h2>
    <p>HTML tables can be used to present data in a structured format. Below is an example:</p>
    <table border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="10">
        <tr>
            <th>Tag</th>
            <th>Purpose</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>&lt;a&gt;</td>
            <td>Defines a hyperlink</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>&lt;title&gt;</td>
            <td>Defines the title of the web page</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>&lt;img&gt;</td>
            <td>Defines an image</td>
        </tr>
    </table>

    <!-- Lists Example -->
    <h2>Creating Lists</h2>
    <p>Lists are useful for summarizing points. HTML supports ordered and unordered lists:</p>
    <h3>Unordered List</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Anchor Tag</li>
        <li>Title Tag</li>
        <li>Image Tag</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Ordered List</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Heading Tags</li>
        <li>Paragraph Tags</li>
        <li>List Tags</li>
    </ol>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <h2>Conclusion</h2>
    <p>
        HTML tags are fundamental to web development and blogging. Practice using these tags to make your blogs more interactive and well-structured.
    </p>
    <p>
        For more resources, check out <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML" target="_blank" title="MDN HTML Documentation">MDN Web Docs</a>.
